; ============================================================================
;						Section keys
;
; MP: 	Offset for reading the actual MP cost of the spell, from the beginning
;		of its routine.
;		If unspecified, it is implied that the cost is always zero.
;
; NOTES:	If specified, this text will appear in the UI when the
;			corresponding spell is selected.
;
; BANK:		If specified, get parameters from this ROM bank instead of the
;			default one.
;
; DESCRIPTION_x:	A string of text that will appear in the UI next to
;					parameter 'x'.
;
; TOOLTIP_x:	A text to show in the tooltip for this parameter's widget.
;
; POINTER_x:	If specified, this will be the base address to the offset for
;				parameter 'x'.
;
; BANK_x:		If POINTER_x is present, it will be the ROM bank where
;				the pointer points to.
;
; OFFSET_x:	Offset for reading parameter 'x' value, either from the
;			start of the spell's routine, or from 'POINTER_x'.
;			For table parameters, this is the offset of the *pointer* to
;			the table, not the offset of the table itself.
;
; TYPE_x:	This determins what kind of widget(s) to show for parameter 'x'.
;			Values can be: HEX (or H), DECIMAL (or D), POINTER (or P),
;			STRING (or S), ATTRIBUTE (or A), BOOL (or B), CHECK (or C),
;			LOCATION (or L), MARK (or M), NPC (or N)
;			For Special Dialogue routines, also: TABLE (or T)
;			Aliases: WORD (or W) is the same as POINTER
;
; SIZE_x:	For TABLE parameters, number of entries (NOT byte count, that will
;			be calculated depending on VALUE_TYPE).
;
; INDEX_TYPE_x:	For TABLE parameters, type of the index value
;				e.g. DECIMAL, HEX, LOCATION, etc.
;
; VALUE_TYPE_x:	For TABLE parameters, type of values contained in the table,
;				e.g. DECIMAL, HEX, POINTER, etc.
;
; TABLE_COPY_x:	For TABLE parameters, if specified each value from the table
;				will be copied to the specified list of offsets upon saving.
;				If the values are 16-bits long, then offsets will be pairs of
;				low, high entries.
; ============================================================================


